^(added_at)$.description: The time when this data object is added to the share, in epoch milliseconds.

^(enable_cdf)$.description: Whether to enable cdf or indicate if cdf is enabled on the shared object.

^(history_data_sharing_status)$.description: Whether to enable or disable sharing of data history. If not specified, the default is DISABLED.
^(history_data_sharing_status)$.title: History Status

^(shared_as)$.description:
If this new name is not provided, the object's original name will be used as the shared_as name.
 The shared_as name must be unique within a share.
 For tables, the new name must follow the format of <schema>.<table>.
^(shared_as)$.title: A user-provided new name for the data object within the share.

^(start_version)$.description:
This allows data providers to control the lowest object version that is accessible by clients.
 If specified, clients can query snapshots or changes for versions >= start_version.
 If not specified, clients can only query starting from the version of the object at the time it was added to the share.

 NOTE: The start_version should be <= the current version of the object.
^(start_version)$.title: The start version associated with the object.
